I've changed the section title from "Premium Features" to "Explore Features", which is more neutral and inviting. This title:

1. Removes the emphasis on premium status
2. Encourages users to explore the app's functionality
3. Maintains a positive, action-oriented tone
4. Is more inclusive for both free and premium users

The rest of the design remains the same, with the streak counter in the header and the balanced 2x2 grid layout for the feature cards. The premium badges are still visible on features that require premium status, but the section title itself no longer emphasizes the premium aspect.

This change makes the interface feel more welcoming to all users while still clearly indicating which features require a premium subscription through the star badges on individual cards.

